      "writtenOn": "2019-05-14T00:00:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "hmm, i iterated through several different names here before choosing the intentionally-vague -resume. :-)\n\n- i initially had names that included \"retry\", but i worried that that would make people think we\u0027re retrying tests, which we don\u0027t do\n- \"reboot\" isn\u0027t completely accurate, as this also resumes testing if the bundle crashes (e.g. because of a panic in a goroutine started by a test) or if the SSH connection is lost due to a networking issue\n- i also had something like -continueonfailure and -continueafterfailure at one point, but i figured those are hard to read",
      "parentUuid": "6fd1658c_076d1668",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 7,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 7,
        "endChar": 18
      },
